And as a hat gets dirtied and frayed from traveling alongside its witch, it becomes imbued with magic." "Now, come a bit closer. Let me teach you a spell to clean the blemishes without washing away the newfound magic." "...It's time to use the cleaning spell you taught me, Grandma! But first, I'll need to gather all the necessary magical tools! If I remember right, I need distilled water, soap, and..."
88.20047:
The usual arcade is filled with excitement, not unlike that of a concert.

"Hehe, I'm on my way to a new high score! Everyone, let me hear you scream!"

In front of a large machine dances a single girl. Her cheerful voice rings throughout the room, and her tail sways in rhythm with her nimble dance steps. I find myself lost in her bright smile—

"Hey! Cheer me on too, okay?"

I feel my heart jump out of my chest. In the next instant, I realize that both her wink and words just now were directed at me.

"And to finish it off, a turn... and a V for victory! Yay, a new high score!"

The machine displays an unbelievably impressive score, and the crowd goes wild. I clap along as well.

"Thanks for cheering me on, everyone! ...Whoa, it's already this late? Let's all meet at the racetrack next time, okay? The mighty Teio will give you a show you won't forget! And with that, I'll take my leave!"

True to her word, the girl abruptly runs out the door. Yet even long after she's gone, the image of her smile is still etched into my mind.

That was probably the moment I became a fan of this little emperor—Tokai Teio.
88.20048:
"Um... are you planning to eat all of that?"

In response to the cameraman's question, Oguri Cap nods with a straight face. However, the fact that her tail is swaying back and forth doesn't escape the eyes of the reporter. At Oguri's level of competition, she must have to train long hours every day, so the reporter asks if this is her way of recharging herself after a long day's work.

Oguri Cap: "No, I just want to eat, that's all. I love eating. Food, eating, and filling up my stomach... I love it all."

Still staring at the food, Oguri Cap's pupils light up like comets glittering in the night sky.

Oguri: "Mind if I begin? Oh, and feel free to try some too. Well then... don't mind if I do!"

With a smile like a flower in full bloom, she digs into the food, and with that, the cameraman is able to catch a rare glimpse of the cool racer's private life.

(Excerpt from Twinkle Monthly, Cover Feature! Oguri Cap—a Peek into the Life of a Racing Idol.)
88.20049:
...I don't want to be known as just some dress-up doll. I want to prove that I can work on something besides my looks.

"Yikes, I burned it again."

There's still so much more I can learn. Like, how to take care of myself, for starters. One day, I won't be just another pretty sight—I'll be the whole package.

"...Right, let's try that again!"
88.30001:
"H-h-hey everybody. Th-thanks for coming out to s-shee us!"

Charmed by the nervous Umamusume's earnest attempt at a greeting, laughter breaks out among the crowd.

"Th-there are so many people!"

"Spe, calm down."

"Yeah, we'll be fine! Just do what we did in practice."

Perhaps calmed by their words, she takes a deep breath and looks out.

"A-as thanks for all your support, I'm going to give today's concert my best!"

Her words are met with cheers. With a smile across her face, she begins the winning concert.
88.30002:
"I was actually... kind of scared. I didn't know what I was supposed to convey to you all."

The venue is completely silent. They sit enraptured, hanging onto every word of the girl standing at center stage.

"I just... love to run. Nothing else interests me."

She hesitates, formulating her next statement.

"But right now, I just want to sing you a song. If I can get through this hurdle, I think I can understand why my heart is pounding so much..."

The song starts to play. She takes a deep breath and reaches out her hand. The answer she seeks is just around the corner.
88.30003:
"Hi, hi! I know we're in the middle of a song, but let's all show some love to the wonderful me! ♪"

Tokai Teio stands at the edge of the stage working up the crowd. She takes a few light steps back to the center and begins the rehearsed choreography.

"I placed first today, meaning center stage is for me! I'm the best and I always will be! ♪"

With the spotlight making her shine all the more, she raises three fingers to the sky.

"My goal to become the undefeated Triple Crown champion is not just a dream! So get rid of those nasty doubts and root for me all the way! ♪"
88.30004: The Golshi battleship has no need for fuel. When fancy strikes her, she takes off like the wind, but she is a fickle being. Go LD-Ship I (A poet, a philosopher, and fearless adventurer/????) "Get out of my way! Move, I say! Move!" All of a sudden, in the final stretch, that devilish silver-haired racer we all thought was in dead last charges forward! "Yahoo! Bada-bing-bada-boom!" Shocking and fearless, she blasts past the finish line and winds up in the North Pole. "Whoops! I missed the K-point! Oh, I'm such a klutz! ☆" Tune in next time for Oden! You'd better be watching!
88.30005: Speaking of which, where is that Umamusume? In that precise moment, she kicks into high gear and faces the last stretch to break the dead heat. "All right! The real race starts here!" Vodka blasts forward from the rear and easily glides past each of the racers. "Hehe! I am the best!" She presses on. Her engine warms as she continues accelerating to full throttle. And then... "Watch and learn, punks! This is what Vodka can do! And don't you dare forget!" Her engines rev and rev and rev until she finishes first. Legends are those who live up to their coolness.
88.30006: "Flowers are like the hearts of plants." Grass Wonder smiles softly as she lightly plucks a flower from its stem. "That's what some people say. Each season stands out because of its most beautiful flowers. And with such beauty, they show us their hearts." Suddenly, her eyes, softened by her smile, begin to narrow. She sticks the last flower in place. "Now, how does that look? I hope my heart will be to your liking." The heart of a gentle girl who hides a mighty fighting spirit stands tall and dignified. A heart that is both delicate and bold.
88.30007:
EL! EL! ELLL!

A lone shadow sways on stage as it is greeted by the aggressive calls of the crowd.

"And in the red corner of the ring! Coming to you all the way from the US of A!
Standing at 163 centimeters and weighing in at none of your business... The masked menace of the ring.
The myth. The legend..."

She flips up her coat and raises a fist into the air!

"The Phantom Bird! ELLLL CONDOOOOR PAAASAAA!"

"YEAAAAAH!"

"You, in the blue corner, ARE YOU READY? Ready to dance?!
Let's give 'em a show to remember!"
88.30008:
By the time her opponents realize this was all part of her plan, it's too late.

"Nyahahaha! I've taken first! ♪"

Just as her opponent rushes forward, Seiun Sky, too, kicks into top speed. The front runner enters the final stretch.

"My run-to-the-front-then-chill strategy worked like
a charm! ♪ Now I can just cruise along."

"I'm going to catch you, Sei!"

"...or not. Ack!"

(Well, I wasn't really intending to make this easy. I'm trying to win too, after all!)

"Catch me if you can! But catching me is like catching 
a cloud. ♪"
88.30009:
"Aw yeah, I'm feelin' a win comin' on!
Hey, hey, hey, hey! Whaddya lookin' at?!"

The little Umamusume Tamamo Cross hops about in the paddock, but no matter how much she leaps and shouts, she barely stands out.

"Look over here, ya jerks! Don't underestimate me just 'cause I'm small!" 

She jumps with everything she's got, straight towards the sky. Finally, just when people start to notice her...

"That's right! Brace yourselves! My runnin's gonna make ya weep for your mommies!"

The audience can't help but smile at her charming antics. In just a few moments, she'll become a strike of lightning.
88.30010:
"Wow. It's so beautiful."

The whole audience sways to the beat of the song. Even the gentle wave of Fine Motion's hand seems to naturally exude elegance.

(After all the excitement of a race, there's still more excitement waiting.)

She experiences a feeling she never dreamed of before, as if she were looking out at something beautiful from her windowsill.

(I want to make more memories with everyone here at Tracen Academy.)

"Racing, dancing, and laughing! I want to do it all! ♪"

You can't find lucky clovers if you don't pursue them!
88.30011: Even as she stands inside the breezy gate, Ines Fujin can't help but think of her family. "Father. Mother. Sisters. Watch me. I'm going to make you all proud!" She bounds out of the starting gate with great power. But perhaps as a result, she sways slightly to the right. (Whoops! But I'm fine!) She kicks back hard and quickly straightens herself. Within moments, her mistake, family, and competitors all disappear from her mind. "Huff... huff... Hahaha!" A gentle breeze? No. A raging storm rushes over the track.
88.30012: With 200 meters left to go, just past the starting line, the best friends reunite. Winning Ticket, ahead of the pack, can feel the heat of the chase without even looking back. "Huff... Huff... Dang it!" "Raaah... Tiiiicket!" (This is so fun! Super-duper fun! Running with Taishin and Hayahide is amazing! I want to run more!) To shake off her best friends, she musters all her strength and lets out a deafening scream. "URRRAAAHHH!" (I won't lose. I won't lose. I CAN'T LOSE! They're my friends—my best friends, so I can't...) "I won't hold back!"
88.30013:
(Not an inch out of line... Time to GO!)

Air Shakur lunges forward in a primal rage. Everyone in the stands sighs, "Again?"
There she goes wasting all her energy on that stupid run of hers. There's no way she can keep it up.

(Or at least, that's what they think...)

However, she doesn't falter and instead accelerates, turning their sighs into visible confusion.

(I knew this would happen. I've calculated just how much stamina I need at this point in the race!)

Her repeated simulations have led her to discover the perfect equation.

"Take this as proof, you idiots!"

The unexpected results shock and anger those around her, but Air Shakur is undeterred. She returns their scorn with mocking laughter.
88.30014: Gold City's golden strands wave in the wind as raindrops slide down her locks. Her breathtaking beauty, apparent even from a distance, is completely obscured by mud. "Just a... little... more!" If she can leave the rest of the runners behind on this last stretch, victory is hers. Yet the ragged breathing of her competition catches up to her, and the muddy track continues to splatter everywhere. (Ah, this is bad. My legs are so heavy! But I have to keep going! I'm so close to winning!) The slightest mistake could throw away her win in this fierce competition, but Gold City's smile shines bright. (Now this is what I'm talking about!) The rain, the mud, the sweat... They are merely accessories. This is the runway where she shines!
88.30015: "BEHOLD! Feast your eyes on the lunchbox of the class representative!" Her eyes beaming, even Sakura Bakushin O's lunchbox seems to exude confidence. It's practically—no, it is bursting with it. "No picnic is complete without sandwiches! They're healthy, colorful... What more could you ask for?" The bread bounces in her hand as she chatters. The cucumber dances. The ham jiggles. "All right. Time to dig in! The picnic's just getting started! Let's eat, then run. OR WHY NOT EAT WHILE I RUN?!" It's then I realize her sakura-colored eyes drawing near. "Bakushin! Let's chow down!"
88.30016:
Here! Have a piece of candy.

...Yes, that's right. I'm talking to Y-O-U. ♪
The one who's staring at me. Please take it.

Hehe, you look nervous. Are you worried about whether I can win or not?

It's true that Oguri and Inari and many other strong racers will be racing as well, but...

I know I'll win. So just sit back and watch.

All right, time to give it my all. If you behave the whooole race and wait until I get back, you'll have earned a few pats on the head. ♪
88.30017:
"Hey, everyooone! Let me hear it! What is it you like about me? ♪"

You're lovely! You're smart! You're super plucky!

"What the heck was that last one? Whatever! ☆ Next, I want you to say my name!"

She's so cute, even when she's running full speed. Oh, Falcooo!

"Now, that's what I wanna hear. ☆ All right then, last one! Say you love me and blow a kiss! ☆"

L-O-V-E!
WE LOVE FALCOOOO!

"Thank youuuu! I'll race to the top, and one day, I'll be the best Umadol!
Just you wait and see! ☆ Mwah! ♪"
88.30018:
"E-everyone...
I have something I want to talk about today!" 

A young and innocent-looking girl tightly grips the microphone. 

"Thank you for all your support!
I'm still new at this, but..."

The small flower begins to bloom.

"I know one day I'll grow up to be a mature and responsible racer!
So please keep watching over me!"

After the concert, many throughout the venue could be heard whispering, "I have to live long enough to see that day."
88.30019: The Ice Cream Song, by Haru Urara Oh, ice cream! Ice cream! It's so fine! An ice cream plushie?! It shall be mine! The crane goes chomp, chomp! It swings but doesn't crumble! Have all the coins we fed it made it big with sturdy muscles? The super strong, invincible, ice cream. Yay! Don't squeeze your ice cream, don't be a fool, But plushies can be cuddled 'cause they're soft and so cool! (Don't lick them though! That's the golden rule!) Every ice cream's tasty, that's understood, Strawberry or orange, melon or grape. Either way, it's all so good, good, good... "Hehe, now I really want some ice cream! Let's go get some! ♪"
88.30020:
"What's this?! The audience isn't getting excited for our concert? Looks like it's time for some justice!"

"Allow me to assist!"

"That voice! It must be..."

"Nutritious! Virtuous! It's the carotene-charged Carrot Ranger! And what’s this?!"

"With wings of justice that slice through evil, she soars through the clouds and makes the skies rumble! Biko Pegasus comes to the rescue! The tag team you've all been waiting for!"

BOOOOOM!

"We must make sure that everyone can smile! It's showtime for justice!"
88.30021:
Good work today, Trainer! My name is Tazuna Hayakawa. I'm the director's secretary here at Tracen Academy. I will do my best to support you from here on, so please do not hesitate to ask me any questions you may have. ♪

Now, without further ado, here are some school documents. Please take a look through them before you start your work.

Here at Tracen Academy, we have a full range of educational resources and facilities to support our Umamusume. Of course, we also have a wealth of knowledge and resources to support your growth as well, so don't worry!

I've been looking forward to working with you. Let's both do our best to make sure the Umamusume are looked after properly!
88.30022:
"Thank you for your support, everyone!"

Mejiro McQueen waves her hand with dignity and grace. The beads of sweat running down her forehead are the only sign of the brutal race that just concluded.

"Winning first place today was another forward step in my journey. I will continue living up to the Mejiro name with every wonderful victory I claim hereafter!"

The audience roars, overflowing with enthusiasm. She then turns away and makes her elegant exit.

(That's it. I'm going to treat myself to cake today. Oh, but what kind should I have?)

Despite her refined behavior, she's still an innocent and sweet girl inside.
88.30023:
(Come on, Rice! You can do it!)

She had thought the only one to cheer her on was herself.

RICE! RICE! RICE! RICE!

But as she dashes past the other racers, like a gift from the heavens, she hears the cheers of many, many people in the stands.

"Oh, I, uh..."

Surprise and confusion overtake her, but finally... she takes one big step forward...

"Th-thank you very much!"

The cheering continues, on and on into eternity.
88.30024:
Hm...

"Yeah. Plushie me is very adorable."

Of course. You—or I guess 'I' was born receiving lots of love, after all.

"Soon, many different people are going to come to take you away. And they will cherish and love you."

"Mama! That Oguri plushie is so cute! I wanna hold her!"

"Oh, looks like it's your time already. All right, I'm counting on you, 'me.' Get all the love and hugs in my place."

We're on it!
88.30025:
Dear Spe,

Thank you for your letter. I can't believe you got lost already! I wonder who you get your total lack of direction from... Make sure you thank Suzuka properly!

I'm glad you've already met someone so kind. Since the two of you are roommates, you won't want to make any trouble for her. So take care not to oversleep or make any messes, okay?

I suppose I can admit this now, but I always worried that you might be lonely living in a place with no other Umamusume. So hearing you've already made a friend makes me so happy!

I hope you make lots more friends and have a great time at school. I'll send your favorites, Spe. (Carrots, of course!) Share them with Suzuka as well.

Stay healthy and stay happy.

Love,

Mom
88.30026:
A girl jumps into the shot.

"Hey, guys! It's me, Turbo! Hey, hey... is this thing workin' right?
It is?! All right, as long as they can see me!
So, anyway, this upcomin' race is gonna be a special one!"

She brings her face closer to the camera. Her sparkling eyes glimmer like thousands of stars.

"I'm gonna wipe the floor with all of 'em! For sure! For sure! I mean it!
I'm gonna dash to the front and win!"

Her voice is bright and hopeful with no signs of worry. Having captured everyone's attention, she proclaims loudly,

"I'm super tough! I'm gonna charge my turbo engines and then WHOOOOSH!
I'll be in first the whole time!"

Maybe it's her naivete shining through, but her words ring reckless... yet innocent.

"I won't lose!"

Perhaps her words are not just a declaration, but a promise to herself. Or perhaps they're meant to encourage those who feel lost.

"So keep your eyes on me!"

Her words echo out forth to everyone on the other side of the screen.
88.30027:
"Ahaha! Get hyped! This could be it!"

Intermixed with the cheers and laughter are lukewarm stares, as if to say, "Them again?" It's nothing new, we're used to it by now. Still...

(Yeah. Everyone gets their chance. Even us. This might be it.)

I feel my toes tighten.
...Interesting. It's as if my whole body is telling me I can go further. What was it that you call this feeling?
That's right! This means I'm getting pumped!

"Whoa! Palmer! This is soooo crazy! You're, like, hella vibing right now!"

Oh, that's it. Yeah, that's what this feeling is. Even hearing the clamor from the audience feels great. I can win, I can keep going. I won't stop. I'm going to run as fast as I can. That's what my body's telling me.
But what if I lose steam before I get there? What if... I can't?

"YOU CAN DO IT! RUN, PALMEEEEER!"

A voice from behind instantly wipes away my fear. We're supposed to be competing, yet she still cheers me on.

(Thanks, Helios.)

Oh... The heat in my body is rising. I still have the energy. I can keep going! I can keep pushing on! Time to kick into high gear, and go, go, go! It's time to surpass my limits!

"Here it comes. Watch me run, run, run away!"
88.30028:
(I knew you'd come, Dia!)

Ahhh, it's as beautiful as I imagined.

I can hear the exhausted pants.
Her kicking footsteps are getting closer.
Those eyes, glimmering like sparkling jewels,
blind me even from behind.
I won't let up, not even for a second.

(I won't let you pass me.)

After all, the road before me is just as bright.

The memory of bitter defeat from being outran by the slightest of margins is still firmly etched in my mind.
We ran with full force and full spirit,
eyes set on the finish line.

I struggled, I felt regret...
But I also had fun.
I'm not going to lose again.
I don't want to lose.

(And yet...)

She's closing in.
Her desire to win...
It draws near, growing hotter and hotter,
until I can feel it blaze across my back.

(Are you having fun too, Dia?)

Soon, you'll be at my side.
And I bet you'll be smiling.
I know because I'm smiling too.
How can you not when having this much fun?
I want to keep on smiling until the very end.
That's why...

"The real race starts now!
And this time, I'm going to win!"
88.30029:
(I'm sure Kita is going to make her move soon.)

Ah, it's so wonderful.

No matter the time, no matter the place,
there she is, running ahead,
leading me forward so patiently.
Her hair and her racewear create a black silhouette, perfectly placed in my line of sight.
And surrounding that shadow... is the light.

(I want to pass her.)

I'm sure what lies ahead is even more dazzling when there's no shadows in the way.

I love it when we walk hand-in-hand.
Laughing, crying, and chasing after our dreams.

Sometimes, as a joke, you dash far ahead. But then, you always stop and ask,
"Are you coming?"

(But still...)

This is a sacred place.
It is a place where we should be civil and sincere.
Even if it's hard, even if we struggle, we must run until the very end.
That is the duty to those chosen for this place.

(But still,
isn't this so fun, Kita?)

I see the determined look on your face when you turn to me with a soft smile.
That's when I'm certain we feel the same. And that's why...

"I am going to win this race!"
88.30030: (Oh, was that a shift in your shoulders? Your legs look a bit unsteady, too. Oh, I see. You're about to kick off!) After an outstanding string of achievements, Matikanetannhauser is now taking part in this race. (I've watched the others run. I've studied their style, their habits, their timing, everything. But...) But such efforts mean nothing to her. It's the least she can do if she wants any chance at overtaking her opponents. (It takes more than that to win. You have to push yourself harder and harder and run faster and faster!) She knows racing is hard. She knows it in her bones how tough it is to win. But that all comes with the territory. She has to step up and push—outrun those two and win. "All right! I'm gonna hit this off with a BANG! "
88.30031:
Yukino! Go for broke!

Hm? Who'm I call'n to?
Look o'er there, it's that girl wav'n at us. The one whose smile just makes your heart melt.

She's like everyone's daughter, help'n to plow our fields and givin' us should'r massages. But most of all... seein' her run always cheers us up. And now it's our turn! We're here to cheer her on!

Huh? You're a fan too? Well, why didn't you say so soon'r? Aw come on, quit your weep'n. Today's s'posed to be happy!

Okey-dokey! Say it with me then! And a one, and a two, and a three...
88.30032:
Training is not only important in martial arts, but for all things in life. Running, dancing, singing, etiquette. Without training, they are like the untilled soil—cold and lacking in vitality.

That day, amidst a great many opponents, this warrior had claimed first place. To stand center stage is an honor that comes with responsibility. It must be done with pride.

The foundation of speech starts in the abdomen. Gather all your power with the soles of your feet planted firmly on the ground, young champion.

The audience wells in anticipation of the coming speech. In the end, she raises her two fists and shout,

"OSU!"

Her companion Sakura Chiyono O is stunned. The faces of the audience and performers break into smiles.

Her duties fulfilled, the warrior takes a deep bow and exit.
88.30033:
I totally thought I was gonna cry! 'Cause, like, ever since I was little, just the thought of this day would bring me to tears.

I'm here—at the winner's interview for the Derby.

But it's strange.
Not a single tear is coming out.
After all, I don't wanna forget this moment.
The sky is blue.
The people in the audience are all cheering and smiling. And I ran my heart out competing with my best friends. I want to remember this all!

I can't waste this time wiping away my tears. The three of us had promised we would race together. We encouraged each other, and we gave it our all. We ran all the way... to the place of our dreams!

"I'm Winning Ticket, the winner of this year's Derby—the best in history!"

But my dreams don't end here! They keep going on, and on, and on!
88.30034:
"U-um... How about we enter through separate entrances and then meet up inside?"

The two part ways and step into the welcoming, sweetly fragrant labyrinth of roses.

...But that was several tens of minutes ago.

The young girl jogs, now slightly out of breath.
She keeps searching and searching, but she can't find what she seeks.
And yet...

(Come on! I can do it! I know I can! I'll be the first to find you...)

(Just like when you found me!)

(I'm going to find you, I promise!)

Just as she turns the corner, her face flushes with joy and breaks into a smile.

"See! I found you!"
88.30036:
The optimal way to guide beginner racers is to manage all aspects of their racing career.

"Why did you decide on stretching when it wasn't in the plan?"

"I was trying to calm my temper. I am sorry that I took some liberties."

Temporary emotional lapses are to be expected. There is no need for concern. More important matters are at hand.

"Excuse me, Trainer Kashimoto! A little light stretching shouldn't affect the plan too much, right?"

"Wrong. It can lead to many problems. You shouldn't be doing anything 'lightly' in the first place.

Training, stretching, diet, sleep... All of these must be taken seriously."

I know the toll a racing life can take. How easily the bridge to one's dreams can crumble. The frigid cold of a lightless path.

"Now then... the runner's tunnel is a bit chilly today. Do another round of warm-ups. That should help."

I will keep up my management. It is my responsibility.
88.30038:
The winner's circle.
The place where only those who prove victorious can stand.

As Sakura Chiyono O makes her way there, she's suddenly blindsided. Her idol, her greatest inspiration, stands before her.

She had marveled at her unparalleled speed and vowed one day that she would stand beside her. And now, through unwavering determination, victory calls Sakura Chiyono O's name.

At a loss for words, she takes careful steps forward as if she were in a trance. The racer who once inspired her smiles softly and reaches out to straighten out her sash.

The afterglow of her victory must have distracted Sakura Chiyono O enough to let it loosen. She blushes as the distance between the two of them shrinks.

Next to this proud and blooming flower, the bud of a tiny cherry blossom opens.
88.30039:
Welcome to the land of dreams, Umander Kingdom.
I'm the princess of this land.

Today is the day that I finally tie the knot with my prince. My people are in high spirits, ready to celebrate.

I stand at the altar, dressed in my gown, as my prince slowly approaches. And just when I reach out to take his hand... 

Out pops out a large throng of enemies and their goons! Of course, the princess, together with the prince, will beat the bad guys to a pulp!

As a princess, and as a bride, I charge into battle!
Happiness is something you must take by fooooorce!

Stubborn again, a tile and a half away,

This precious moment will abruptly end

I run. And run. And run... But it's not enough to pass the obstacles between us, let alone catch her.

I turn. Again. Again. Around I go... Up... and down. My mind reels—colors blur past—like I'm running atop a giant gear.

And then, I hear someone singing. It's beautiful... but the song isn't meant for me. I think... this whole time, I wasn't looking ahead of me. I was just watching her back.

That's right. All I saw was her. I couldn't see anything else. I wasn't running cleanly—I was running desperately, frantically... just trying not to lose sight of that faint shadow.

There's something stirring in me, diluting the essence of what I was. Transforming me into another gear on the track, chasing her loop after loop.

With each revolution, I lose more of myself. The clamor feels so far away. I can't make out whether the blurred mob shouts in cheer or fury.

As it all melts together into an indiscernible cacophony, one thing alone remains quiet and true—a thin thread—the path cleared in your wake.

(You're still there. And I'm still following!)

The golden disc beneath us whirls. I reach out, stretching my hand to hers—

...And in that moment, I left the world behind.

I can't quite place when or where the episode took place. I've racked my memories to no avail.

And so... It must have been something I saw in a dream. Some sort of nightmare—something dreadful I hoped would never come to pass.

I'm confident in that answer.

...Because when I open my eyes again, I see something completely different.

"Silence Suzuka! Silence Suzuka has done it again! A stunning runaway victory!"

I'm not really interested in daydreaming up what-ifs or letting nightmares cloud my vision.

I want to see new scenery—unimaginable ones—and I want to see it with my own two eyes.

Today. Tomorrow. Every day. Forever!

"HAAAHAHAHA! That look on your face—it's plain as day! You're over the moon for these sweets!"
88.30084: "Um, do I spread my fingers like this?" "Yep, just like that. Hang tight while I do the other hand, m'kay?" Is Flower even enjoying this? I have like literally no idea if this is the right way to cheer her up... I mean, when do I ever think before I act? Why won't the right words come to me? Why is it so hard to come up with something she'd like? But... Ugh, I can't just leave her hanging. I've gotta do something to help. Something... So I guess I'll just do what I do best and hope it works out. "Wow, it's so pretty! I feel like a big grown-up lady now!" "Wait, for real? Like you actually like it?" "Of course! My nails look amazing!" Whoa, nailed it! Guess it just goes to show that sometimes thinking gets you nowhere. You've just gotta give things a go!
88.30085: We're at a meet and greet for a popular Umadol. With a copy of the new album in hand, Agnes Digital gets in line for a signature. "Oh no... Oh noooonono aaaaashjsd?! Her hair is so glossy... I'm definitely seeing a real halo there! Omg, I think she might actually be an angel!" "I can't believe she's here, in person... breathing the same air as us humble simps... How saintly! How benevolent!!!" "Aaasdh wait, the closer the line gets, the clearer I can see her! Hwaaaah, the photo on the album cover's gorgeous, duh, but she's like a million billion times more radiant in person..." "I'm ascending... Take me up, sweet ange—Gasp. I-I almost actually ascended there for a second. She's radiating dangerous levels of moe and I'm not sure I can get any closer—HELP." "All right. Okay. Just stay calm. Focus... This is no time to be swooning! I've gotta simulate the convo in my head so I don't say anything weird to her." "Okay, so I've gotta walk up there confidently, y'know like normal confident but not so much that it looks unnatural, right? And then she'll sign the album, and then I'll say, 'Thank you! I'm always cheering for you!' and then get outta the way lightning fast so I don't take up any of the next fan's time... Yeah. That's the plan." "We've all gotta be on our best behavior, or they might not do signings for us anymore... I've gotta make a good impression and show her what an honor it is to simp for her! I've got this!! Hang tight, I'm up next!!!!!!" With that, Agnes Digital walks forth gallantly, as though I'm watching a knight approach her lord. Bold, and strong... I think.
88.30086: 3,000 long, stamina-draining meters. A long, perilous slope stretching from the third corner. A difficult track that cannot be conquered with effort alone. A stream of sweat drips from her brow, threatening to blur her vision. Her heart beats frantically, like it's screaming for more oxygen to pump through her veins. Each rough breath scratches at her throat like flickers of flame. She asks herself why. Why does she keep running, when it hurts so much? Why does she continue to drag her heavy legs step after arduous step? Her mind doesn't have time to process an answer. But her ears flick unconsciously towards a rumble from the stands. A roar of cheers—of fans' hopes and dreams. She then clenches her teeth, biting down into the pain, and spitting it out. A sense wells in her gut—her fated rival is behind her. The large shadow she casts over the turf is getting closer. Closer. Closer. But she knows she can't look back. She won't give up. The only way to reach the peak is to keep running. ...And that day, the runner who refused to surrender took the crown of the best.
88.30087: "Huh? Is this thing... Oh no, Bright! Bright, stop! That's enough! ...I'm so sorry. I think the timer's display is messed up." "Huff... Huff... Whew. Now that you mention it, that last set felt oddly long." "Oh gosh... That was probably as long as three sets. A-are you okay?" "Mm-hm, just peachy." "You still have stamina after all that?! You must be really on top of your training! Do you think you still could have kept going if I didn't stop you?" "Ehehe, probably. Honestly, I probably wouldn't have noticed the timer wasn't working if you hadn't said anything." "Ahahaha! That's so like you! I guess some things never change. Hehe... Maybe it's because of how long I've known you, but seeing you crush that set has me all happy." "That's sweet of you to say. It's a good thing I've been training hard to live up to the Mejiro name. I suppose I'll have to keep on improving myself, little by little."
88.30088:
"So, how's it been since you two came to Tracen? Is it different than you expected?"

"Yes... It certainly isn't anything like I imagined. What about you, Kita?"

"Same. It's way different from what I thought."

"Huh? I-in a good way or a bad way? I hope you two aren't disappointed..."

"No, of course not. If anything... It's been far lovelier than I could have dreamed! The training, the races—everything's been so magical!"

"Yeah, me too! With all the exciting stuff going on, it feels like every day's a festival!"

"Whew... That's good to hear. You had me worried for a second. But... I think I was the same way when I first came here too. All this fancy new stuff left 'n right, and special things happening one after another... Tracen's still full of surprises even for me!"

"Really? Even though you've been here so much longer than us?! Ooh, what're we gonna do, Dia?"

"Don't look at me—I'm just as curious as you are!"

"Ahaha, I'm sure there will always be big, wonderful surprises in store for all three of us!"

"Right!"
"Right!"
88.30089: The stands are roaring with excitement. In the crowd, one man whispers excitedly to himself in a trembling voice. "I've been waiting for this moment... She had high expectations placed on her, but she was never able to take home the gold... Just like me. But now, she's finally won... Because she believed in herself and never gave up." "Was that marvelous enough for everyone? ☆ All of you are looking oh-so marvelous as well! ★☆★" Warm tears run down the man's cheek. He has finally realized the truth that has been lying in front of him the whole time... "I'm... marvelous, too..." And so, another marvelous light is born into this marvelous world.
88.30090: Your fangs threaten to sink into me with every step. Your graceful movements resemble a predator waiting for the right moment to strike the fatal blow. "I see that you're as sharp as ever. Perhaps you've been keeping up your training? How admirable." "Right, for once. Someone's got to protect our spoiled little Emperor from the eyes of the masses, now don't they? Not like you could do anything without being pampered." "Allow me to correct one of your statements. As I'm unable to resolve this matter expediently, I'll simply march to the beat of your drum for now." It's your turn, and the silence is deafening. I see your scorn replaced by apathy, when suddenly, a light bulb flashes above your head. "If that's how you want to play, then fine by me. But don't forget—you asked for this!" "Oh, such risky footwork! The most important thing between partners, Sirius, is trust. And so you don't forget it anytime soon, it's time for your private lesson." I can see your desire for control in each of your aggressive steps. In response, I will bring all I have and match you at every turn. Do not forget—you stand in the presence of the Emperor, Symboli Rudolf.
88.30091:
...Hey, what do you see from there? Sluggish shadows drifting through the night? Or perhaps dust from the dance floor, kicked up by someone's fancy footwork?

"Mhm, in there you'll only find a tent of tedium, spread around like a sloshy quagmire. They've only two choices—accept their muddy fates and sink, or writhe in vain defiance. How drab."

"However, I can present you with a third choice. Take my hand... and I'll show you how much fun this world can be."
88.30092:
Energy equals mass times the speed of light squared. In the end, everything comes down to equivalent exchange. What goes around, comes around. In other words, no matter how hard you try, you won't get any more than you put in... and that's fine by me.

"This is getting me hyped! It doesn't get better than !monad! Wooooo!"

That said, when needless noise gets mixed into the equation, all of that balance goes straight to chaos! But I won't stop...

"Fine by me. You want more? I'll give you more. I'll overload your senses until you drop!"

I live in a cache full of unknown variables...

"Come on, follow my groove! Ha... haha!"

Why am I trying so hard to suppress my laughter? ...Tch, guess I was the one being played. Well, I've solved the equation, so I'll pay my respects.

"...Until this beat of mine dies down, don't turn on the lights."
88.30093: I'm a fan of wearing blue and white. It's refreshing, but vibrant. Elegant, but not too pretentious. It's the number one color combo for the me I want to be. "Mhm, just like I thought—this is the number one fit for me! ♪" My outfit's all set. The frills and pleats look good, and I tied the big bow perfectly. A quick posture check... oh, and can't forget the smile! Yup, this is it—this is undoubtedly what an honor student on her day off looks like! "This is an important outing, so I have to make sure to go in my number one outfit! ♪"
88.30094:
You're always cheering somebody on. You encourage them, scold them, and share in their ups and downs.

Even today, you're cheering on someone from the stands up above. Despite waving a banner weighing easily over ten kilograms, you and everyone in the cheer squad continue cheering with your eyes fixed on the race, no matter how raspy your voices get.

You stand in the shadows, where light will never reach.

And yet, you continue exerting every last drop of your strength, all to fulfill your duty. You believe it's simply the right thing to do, and you take great pride in upholding this duty.

"Keep it up."

Suddenly, three words slip out of my mouth. They are spoken softly, quiet enough to be drowned out by even the sounds of everyday life. Words fated to drift away, and reach no other ears.

But then you turn around and face me, still waving your banner, and still cheering the racers on. It's only for an instant, as fleeting as the swaying of a flame in the wind, but I see it—your bright smile shining straight at me.
88.30095:
An exciting race unfolds itself before me as I watch from the stands up high. Every racer is bursting forward with impressive speed. Out of the blue, a strikingly loud voice rings throughout the venue.

"Nice turn! But they're hot on your heels! At this rate... Ah!"

I wonder who she's cheering for. She sounded pretty crushed just now...

"Good job, what a beautiful pass! I can tell you've been working on that! Now take it home—gooo!"

"Huh?! Weren't you cheering for the racer who was in the lead until now?"

The words spill out of my mouth, and the girl, Seeking the Pearl, looks at me with a warm smile.

"In a race, there'll always be a winner and a loser. There's always two sides, like light and darkness. But you know, when it comes to competitors giving it their all, everyone's the same, and I think we should celebrate that! Every racer deserves to be cheered for and praised! I support each and every one out there!"

Her words are pure and innocent, like a pearl. And in the face of her brilliance... I begin to see the world through a new lens.
88.30096: If I slip up even a little, they'll be hot on my heels. But wait, this sudden ovation of cheers during my most dire moment... This is just like... "Princess Fighter! Don't give up!" I'm in her shoes today, with everyone rooting for me the same way I used to cheer at the TV. "Now, Princess Fighter—punish evil!" She's the definition of a perfect princess, and my idol. "Gooo, Princess Fighter!" There's only one path left for me, for you see, a princess... "Never, ever loses!"
88.30097:
The track was in the worst possible condition. Even so, you treaded through the mud, broke out of the pack, and took the lead when no one else could.

Not even upturned turf, fierce rain, or racers blocking the way could stop you. You simply weaved your way past each competitor, leaving them behind, one after the other.

And each time you passed another racer, your sky-blue eyes shone brilliantly, as if you yourself had become like the vast sky—soaring freely forward, always just out of reach...

"Mr. C.B. finishes in first place! Mr. C.B. takes it all here at the first race of the Triple Crown!"

In that whirlwind of rain and mud, when visibility was at its worst, you stood above everyone else.

And then like a child, you wiped the mud off your cheek with the back of your hand, before slowly curling the corners of your mouth into an easygoing smile. Turning to the crowd, you stood tall and raised your hand to the sky.

Seeing that pose, the fresh memories of my bitter defeat instantly faded away, replaced by your gallant figure etched into my mind.
88.30098:
Brand new racewear for me! ♪ A first-place winner I'll be!

"With my racewear, I'm so happy! Running, running, yay! ♪"

"Hop, skip! Skip, hop! ♪ I'll give it my all, like 'blaaam!'"

A girl from my class is singing something to herself. It's not the first time she's done this, but for some reason, I find myself especially curious about her song today.

"...What kind of song are you singing?"

I walk up to her and ask a simple question. She looks like she's having so much fun, and her energy is infectious.

"Oh, it's my racewear song! I'm really looking forward to wearing it at my next race! I'll give it my all, like 'blaaaam!'"

She's singing because she's excited. And she's excited because she's going to run. Her explanation is so simple, but it resonates with me deeply.

"Good for you."

At some point, I forgot what it felt like to run for fun.

"Hey, do you wanna sing with me? Here, I'll count us in!"

"Whoa, r-right now?"

"A one, and a two! Hop, skip! Skip, hop! I'll give it my all! ♪"

"L-like 'blaaaam...'"

"Like 'blaaam!' Hehe, I can't wait for my next race!"

It's funny, I've only sung a single line with her, but I already feel a bit happier.

Right, races are supposed to be fun. There's no need to worry about the details. I just need to go out there and have fun!
88.30099:
Wow... Ikuno, you look so pretty... Just like a real bride!

"Thank you, Rice."

Wearing such splendid racewear in front of everyone... is making me surprisingly self-conscious. Still, this kind of opportunity doesn't come by every day. I just need to make it through this photo shoot...

"What?! Ikuno, you're getting married?! No way, since when?! I don't want you to gooo!"

"Huh? What're you doing, Turbo?! Look, you're getting in the shot, silly!"

"Nooo waaaaay! Don't leave me behiiind!"

Due to Turbo's misunderstanding, the photo shoot has been rendered into a state of mild disarray. That said, hearing the star front runner Turbo cry "Don't leave me behind!" is amusing in it's own way.

"Turbo, please calm down. I'm not going anywhere."

There's no way I'd leave now. After all, we're still in the middle of a race of our own.

Once we're done taking photos, I think I'll join Turbo and the others in their training.
88.30100:
Once upon a time, I went to a wedding.

When the bride smiled gently, the people around her also started smiling, and everyone was as happy as they could be. I'll always treasure that wonderful memory.

One day, I want to make everyone smile like that. I want to spread happiness to everyone around me. It's not much, but that's my dream.

I'll gather up my courage... and take that big step forwards. And once I do, I'll see smiles everywhere I look.

It'll be just like what the bride saw at that wedding—the sight of happiness. Up until now, I've only gotten a glimpse of that view.

"...I want to keep on making people smile."

I hope to keep on putting smiles on everyone's faces, so that someday, everyone can find their very own happiness.
88.30102:
Dober's way too nice. She's always overthinking things and worrying about others.

Why do I know this? Because she's saved me so many times with her kindness and thoughtfulness!

"...Let the match begin!"

Entering the ring from the red corner, we have Tracen Academy's Phantom Bird—Masked El!

And in the blue corner, we have her opponent, Señorita Mejiro—Worrywart Dober!

The rules are simple! Listen to Dober, talk with her, and make her smile for a perfect ring out! ...Haha, I've got this one in the bag!

"After all, with this mask on, I'm pumped up, confident—invincible, even!"
88.30103:
In a picturesque forest, two Umamusume swing from a single vine, riding the wind.

"Um, Taiki?"

"What's up? Somethin' in your noggin?"

"There's something I've always wanted to try if I ever got into a situation like this... Well, more like say? Or even shout? Anyways, there's something!

"Roger that, Tannhauser! We're birds of a feather!"

"Right! Then, on three... One, two... three!

"Ahhhhh! ♪"
88.30104:
A water spirit's shoreline, a fairy's secret garden, and a door only revealed by starlight... After overcoming countless trials, the townspeople had finally reached their destination. And now, in front of them, was the most beautiful sight in the world...

"Well, I'll be! The walls are glowing baby blue!"

"It's like we've entered another world... Who knew a place like this existed?"

Faced with such a dreamlike scene, the townspeople could only open their mouths in awe and say...

"Ahhh, this is it! We've really entered the world of that story!"
88.30105:
To become the best racer in all of Japan.

That was my dream. It was my everything—what I'd promised to my moms.

Still, dreams are funny things, aren't they? I wanted to grab hold of mine, but like mist on a cold morning, no matter how hard I tried, I couldn't. All I could do was try my hardest—to keep on reaching for something that couldn't be reached.

But it was worth it.

All of my experiences—everyone I've met along the way—helped make my dreams come alive! I've had nail-biting races against my rivals, and I overcame hurdles inside of me that I thought I couldn't. There's been tough times, even sad times. But there's also been fun times and happy times. Everything I've been through has helped shape my dream!

Do you have a dream? Or maybe a burning desire? Then let's go chase it together! I'll help make your dreams come true!
88.30106:
If she wins this race, then both mother and daughter will have conquered the Japanese Oaks—an unheard-of feat. The venue is filled with both expectations and doubts, each weighing heavily on this one racer's shoulders.

But the moment the Empress takes to the turf, all the commotion is blown away in a burst of wind. For her, even the wind is but another of her subjects. She heads towards the starting gate with confident strides.

Her sharp eyes demand absolute fealty from all who face her. Her fingers clench into a fist so tight her nails dig into her skin.

She desires perfection. She hungers for victory. Her pride as Empress is her weapon.

"This race is mine for the taking."
88.20022: Heh, now this is the good stuff! Light, soft, and chewy! Heh, nobody grills squid quite like Kansai does. I swear, people here in the East just throw the whole squid on the grill and call it done, y'know what I mean? But this is how it's supposed to be done. I loved 'em when I was little, y'know. Used to eat it all the time growin' up! ...Whaddya mean, I'm still little?! ...Yeesh, if that's how you're gonna be, maybe I won't share any. Hehe, aw, I'm just kiddin'. I'm a bigger person than that. Here! Now... how do ya like it? I toldja it was the good stuff!
88.30043: White or black. Heads or tails. Win or lose. The gates flip open like the toss of a coin. Everything's up in the air—until someone crosses the finish. Or at least, it should be. But the big races aren't so simple. People've just gotta play favorites and make a fuss over who's gonna win. You really think the favorite's gonna win just 'cause she knows how to do a little fan service? What a joke. Races wouldn't be any fun if you knew the winner before it even started. Once the die's cast, the rest'll be up to Lady Luck. Those racers are going all-in for just a two-minute shot at glory—no guarantees. And that's what makes races exciting. Now... you'd better watch those gates. The fanfare'll start any second now.

120.1: Dengan deklarasi yang menggemparkan, ketua akademi Akikawa membentuk perlombaan baru bernama <color=#FF6D26>Final URA</color>! Para trainer dan Umamusume bekerja sama untuk menjadi juara pertamanya!
120.2: Saat Umamusume Buat Tim Baru! <color=#FF6D26>Unity Cup</color>. Tapi sebelum keseruan dimulai, akademi menghadapi krisis Tim!? Bantu Trainer Untuk Menangkan Kejayaan Akademi
120.3: Kenapa Umamusume bernyanyi di konser? Seorang produser tiba-tiba muncul dan mengusulkan rencana baru — <color=#FF6D26>Grand Live</color>. Bantu Uma-mu Jadi Seorang Idol
120.4: Perlombaan baru yang dibentuk oleh media — <color=#FF6D26>Twinkle Star Climax</color>. Pertarungan untuk menentukan yang terkuat! Berlari menuju klimaksmu sendiri, kejar impianmu!
120.5: Saat Latihan  Seperti Biasanya Tiba-Tiba datang 3 dewi Umamusume . Siapa Mereka ?<color=#FF6D26>Grand Master</color>. Turnamen ini ?
120.6: Prix De l'Arc de Triomphe, puncak balap internasional. Mereka yang mencari kemenangan di puncak dunia setiap tahun. <color=#FF6D26>Project L'Arc</color>,
120.7: No.1 UAF Tournament jadillah umamusume terbaik dalam hal olahraga ! Oh iya , banyak latihan menarik dan fans yang menunggu peampilanmu
120.8: Suatu Hari Direktur Akikawa Mempunyai Ide untuk Membuat Kegiatan OSIS untuk Mengelola ladang di Akademi Tracen !
120.9: Seorang Gadis Mechauma muncul di Akademi Tresen. Robot ini diciptakan oleh Dr. Sugarlights yang jenius. Robot ini masih model awal dan masih banyak masalah yang harus diatasi... tapi mari kita perkuat dan wujudkan impian sang dokter!
120.10: Saat Seri Twinkle terancam, Umamusume yang "legendaris" bangkit! Semua pihak yang terlibat dalam dunia balap akan bersatu untuk mempopulerkan Seri Twinkle kembali - dan di masa depan!
120.11: Sebuah proyek pulau terpencil tiba-tiba dimulai. Kejar impian Tucker Brine, Dengan membantunya membangun tempat latihan di tempat terpencil.
120.12: Liburan Sudah Dekat ! Para Umamusume Ingin Liburan Ke Onsen . Tapi ,<color=#FF6D26> Onsen Dalam Masalah ?! </color>. Apakah Trainer Bisa membantu untuk masalah ini ?

128.1044: Become the top umadol! Euphoria, cuteness, and poppy on the mic!♪ Smile wide and sing along☆
128.1055: Lookie there! That a ship?! A UFO!? Nein, it's Golshi!!! Peace Peace♪ Howboutthat? All your base are belong to me☆
128.1056: A solemn chorus sung by the Mejiro family. Their splendor reaches far and wide—
128.1156: Berkat kalian semua―『Aku sudah tumbuh sebesar ini♡』Terima menu ucapan terima kasihku yang penuh cinta ini♡ Silakan dinikmati ya♪
128.1175: $(nb)Hari-hari saat kita berjuang. Tak terasa, kita melangkah sejauh ini. Ikatan yang berdampingan, akan membawa kita melampaui mimpi yang tak berujung—
128.1001: A high-energy song perfect for the URA Finals. Let me hear you shout! Umapyoi! ♪ Umapyoi! ♪
128.1004: Our rivalry is what brought us together... And now there's no stopping us! Never looking back!
128.1005: A song only those who wear the Triple Tiara can sing. A flowery song filled with determination.
128.1006: The first song sung by Umamusume after their debut. Echo forth! Fanfare!
128.1007: A refreshing song sung by rising stars in their junior year. The racers' dreams sparkle brilliantly.
128.1008: Only those who keep their eyes on the prize will reach the NEXT FRONTIER. The crown awaits...
128.1009: A powerful song for those who power through and win the day. Not even a raging storm will stop them.
128.1010: As if flowers will bloom from this very tune, this music captures the beautiful moment of a G1 triumph. Chase your dreams, and they will come true!
128.1012: Whether we're racing or just running for the fun of it, we give the track everything we've got! We gathered up all the unique dreams we have, and put them into this song, so let's go! Starting gate!
128.1023: Sometimes we fight, and we don't know how to make up. But deep down, we'd rather be smiling together. No matter how blue or bitter we feel, that's just part of being friends—and this song is a reminder of that!
128.1025: A song where the brightest star can shine, one of bravery and hope. An exciting new feeling... A signal of new beginnings.
128.1026: A song filled with a fleeting yet strong will. With a wish in her heart, she makes a plea to the moon.
128.1027: They vowed to be the fastest! The racers, running beyond their limits, follow their instincts and shout!
128.1028: A song those who wear the Classic Triple Crown can sing. Performing this is every racer's dream.
128.1030: Watching you encourages me to race on to victory! An energetic song about enjoying every moment!
128.1031: An intense song about the storm of emotions that captivates racers. It's impossible not to give in.
128.1032: A refreshing song performed with a rival. Placing your dreams in another, a new story begins...
128.1035: Now that I know I never was alone... A song that celebrates the smiles and tears born of friendship.
128.1034: The life of a racer is full of ups and downs, smiles and frowns... so we squeezed all the big, wacky adventures of Tracen life into one itty-bitty song! ♪
128.1037: What lies beyond the goal? What unique scenery is there to see there? This song blends wonder and warmth, gently encouraging you to keep on running.
128.1042: This song is about the dreams we have, and the resolve it takes to keep running toward them. It's about moving forward, even when you're lost or scared. If you ever lose your way, we're here to tell you, "Go this way."
128.1043: This one's the story of two Umamusume. Out in the freezing rain, they huddled together and made a promise—"It's not over yet—we still can shine, if our dreams are on the line and you're by my side..."
128.1048: We all start in the same gates. The path opens to any who would run it—so go! Surge ahead, with the tailwind urging you on!
128.1049: Bakushin! Bakushiiin! BAKUSHIIIIIIN! This song was written by Bakushin for Bakushin, and I hope it will inspire some BAKUSHIIIN in you too!\n—Comment from Class Representative
128.1050: Our first anniversary... We really poured all our gratitude into this song. It's about reaching our dreams, and finding new inspirations beyond them. We'll keep running with you, further and further!
128.1040: This song shines with all that makes youth so dazzling—friendship, rivalry, tears, smiles, doubt, and hope.
128.1051: Dreams come to those who run on! An ode to the radiance of youth and all the tears and smiles it brings.
128.8501: BGM for the StarHorse TV news program. If you hear this song start playing, it's time to find out what's new with StarHorse4!
128.8502: You can't have a StarHorse allowance race without this fusion tune. An homage to the evolution of the series.
128.8503: If this song plays during your debut, you know you're in for a show! Getting this song to play is a goal for any StarHorse4 player.
128.8504: BGM that plays during breeding in StarHorse4. Craft your ideal pedigree at your leisure with this relaxed tune.
128.8505: BGM that plays during breeding in StarHorse4. The music seems to grow along with your horse and pairs well with the cutscenes.

228.99: Now, it's music time～♪ \nWhich song is Trainer-san's favorite～?
228.149: Hm, hmm, hm～ hnn～…\nOh my, am I too slow～?
228.150: Here we go～! When Falcon runs～? One, two… "We run after her!" Ehe♪ Thanks everyone☆
228.151: Wah～ They're all great songs! Tell me your favorite, trainer♪
228.152: Eyy don't run off, listen! The waves'll leave a Golshi shaped impression on your eardrums…☆
228.153: This tone reverberates in my heart. What sort of tracks do you prefer, Trainer?
228.154: Music keeps me running! \nWhat songs do you like to run to?
228.155: Oho, what a great selection of tracks \nI see you have great taste～!
228.156: Put on something energetic to dance to!
228.157: Huh, I like this track! The sounds are filling my head with amazing magics!
228.158: Music? …I don't hate it. Lets me shut out the noise.
228.159: Hearing these songs reminds \nme of my rivals!
228.174: Songs that bring luck change \nwith time! Isn't that interesting?
228.175: Now that's a spiffy tune…! \nI can't wait ta be a "city girl" \nbefitting of them vibes～…!
228.176: What a very, very nice song～! \nWhat dance would fit it?
228.183: DJ Heli in da house! \nPut your hands up, it's party time!
228.184: Gotta go fast, WEEEII! \nI wanna have a blast singing \nmy lungs out with Milady again～♪
228.187: This sound is special to me. Like a gust \nof wind rushing through my heart, leaving \nits lingering scent... I cherish it.
228.1: This song really gets me going! Getting to sing this song is like proof you're number one in Japan! So I've gotta try harder!
228.2: My mom loves this song! She said it's the one that made her cry the most when she saw me singin' it... Hehe.
228.3: Ooh, I like this song too!
228.4: Oh, I remember doing this song... It was giving me trouble, but Air Groove was kind enough to help out.
228.5: This song takes all the weight off my legs. I feel like I could just take off and run forever and ever...
228.6: This song... seems like it could be pretty good to run to.
228.7: This song always makes me feel much braver. ♪ It won't be easy getting to where I wanna go!
228.8: The legend of the invincible Teio goes on! You and I are never gonna stop runnin' for our dream. ♪
228.9: Hey, what song are you thinkin'? I'm in a good mood, so lemme show ya my special Teio step. ♪
228.10: Must be nice to have a rival always by your side... Just thinking about it gets my heart pumping. ☆
228.11: The chorus is totally rad! Singing it is like zooming down the road at top speed!
228.12: Look at all these hip tunes! I bet these would be totally fly at the disco too. ☆
228.13: An endless dream is what I hope to show my fans. And you as well, of course! Do look forward to it.
228.14: This takes me back to my beginnings... when I stepped off the stage and onto the turf.
228.15: Which song is your favorite? I'd love to know!
228.16: The dance solo gets my heart racing. I... don't mind this feeling.
228.17: If there comes a future day when I overcome all my limits... what then? I can't wait to find out.
228.18: Thinking about what song to pick made me hungry...
228.19: This song reminds me of that old saying: "Two times a winner, double the chicken dinners."
228.20: Even while we were recording this, Scarlet and Vodka were going at it. Luckily, I had my fishing net on hand.
228.21: Cue some bangers, 'cause it's time to play flounder othello!
228.22: No speed, no life! I'm gonna keep my engines firing, and you're coming along for the ride!
228.23: The chorus is so sick! You can really feel the "smoldering embers" of Brian's soul!
228.24: Hey, this thing has all the coolest songs. Wanna listen?
228.25: Winning is obviously important, but dancing alongside your rivals is, well... I don't hate it.
228.26: Don't read too much into the lyrics, you hear? It's not how I actually feel. Like, at all. Got it?!
228.27: All the songs here are worth a listen!
228.28: A mile seems long, but you can blink once and it'll all be over... Time flies on the track!

228.32: We all have our own reasons for running, but ultimately our hopes all come down to one thing: winning.

228.36: Teach, sing with me! I'm not taking no for an answer!

228.40: Instinct versus instinct, clashing on the course! Ring the bell, 'cause a battle royale is about to begin!
228.41: Whose legend? El's legend! Whether it's spring, summer, fall, or winter, El is the world's strongest!
228.42: The melody, the beat, the excitement! Let's enjoy this music together!
228.43: Down this perilous path I walk, toward my promised throne at the top! O, to possess such strength and beauty must be a sin!
228.44: On that fateful day when I performed this song, racing history—nay, the entire world lurched forward into a new dawn!
228.45: Even now I hear it... a chorus of praise for the overlord!
228.46: I don't need titles. I run to win... That'll never change.
228.47: No more doubts... Watch me. I'll show everyone who I am.
228.48: How long are you going to take? Hurry up and choose.
228.49: I'm rather fond of such displays of passion on stage as hoisting the microphone, stand and all. Heh, does that surprise you?
228.50: Music... muse sick? No. Hmm... Oh, don't mind me.
228.51: What? A smile is simply part of the performance, and an important one at that. Of course I'd have it down perfectly.
228.52: Take your time. It's a difficult choice, what with so many masterpieces.
228.53: No way. This song was literally made for all of us who just want to "witness" Uma greatness! Thank you, URA... I could cry...
228.54: Wait, is this... the gateway song that so many non-believers got Uma-pilled on? It's so peak!
228.55: Are you gonna play your oshi's song? I'm all ears!
228.56: No one likes a predictable race. It's all about telling destiny who's boss and shocking the crowd.
228.57: Ahh, a song of hopeful beginnings. Maybe I'll set out on a journey of my own... into the land of dreams.
228.58: Oh, you taking a break too? Well, kick back and put on some tunes.
228.59: A clash of destinies... I have no intention of ceding center stage, but I suspect neither of them do either.
228.60: I'll always be there to take your hand, so long as you offer it. That's what an older sister is for.
228.61: Now then, which song will you choose? I'm curious to see your tastes.
228.62: I love this song. ♪ The stage looks like a cake, and you get to make a heart with your hands—it's so cute!
228.63: Tehe. ♪ Every song gets my heart racing when I'm listening with you. Funny how that works!
228.64: Passion... I felt it with both mind and body... its true meaning.
228.65: This takes me back... I can't believe it's been so long... Wonder how that owl's doing...
228.66: Ah... My friend likes that one too...
228.67: Win or lose, you only get to stand on those stages once. The emotions of such moments can only be expressed through song and dance.
228.68: ...Her prayer will be answered. I can't analyze why, but I am sure of it.
228.69: Commencing Operation Audio Sample... These are fascinating sound waves.
228.70: I want to shine just like them and set a special record of my own... All right, it's bulking season!
228.71: Hey, you should try lifting while you listen to music. You'll get fit, and have fun while doing it!
228.72: A full-out clash of speed, and smiles at the end of the stretch... Ingredients for the perfect sumo stew!
228.73: Ohh, there are so many good songs! ♪ It's like music à la mode!
228.74: I've made my choice... I'm going to go down this path, and bring happiness to all!
228.75: When they were composing this song, the artists interviewed me... They really respected my feelings.
228.76: Hehe, I don't even know where to begin. Which one's your favorite?
228.77: Hehe, I don't even know where to begin. Which one's your favorite?
228.78: Blinding speed... Do they mean the speed of light, perhaps? Yes, that's it... we can learn from photons and their constant ways!
228.79: The electronic beeping comforts me. Just like the brain wave measurements I took while listening to this—pure euphoria!
228.80: Oh, keep browsing. I'm just gathering some data.
228.81: The choreography is really hard! I went all out shaking my tail and then... Aghh, just thinking about it hurts!
228.82: Taishin and Hayahide are always there for me when I need a good cry! That's what lets me keep barreling forward!
228.83: I like songs that hit you with a "bang!", but songs that are like "bam!" are cool too, don't you think?!
228.84: I too have a dream deep in my heart. Until that crown of glory is in my hands, I won't let anything stop me.
228.85: Toll... ♪ All these songs are so wonderful, I don't know which to choose.
228.86: I'm gonna run down the stretch hardest of all, and cross the finish with the cutest smile! My dream is right there in the lyrics. ♪
228.87: Everyone's been using the intro as music for their Umasta stories lately. Guess who started the trend. ♪
228.88: What do you wanna listen to? Maybe you could pick out a cute song for me. ♪
228.89: What do you wanna listen to? Maybe you could pick out a cute song for me. ♪
228.91: This song reminds me of the day I made up my mind to become a princess... those first steps of mine.
228.92: My, what a delightful song! It's got me itching to throw a few punches!
228.93: I like how bubbly the song is overall, but like... do we really have to shake our tails like that?
228.94: Huh, guess I'll get to see what you're into. Well, don't keep me in suspense.
228.95: Hryahh! Wahh! Woohoo! Well, what do you think? I tried putting the song's emotions into words—with some Bakushin flair!
228.96: C'mon, Trainer, sing it with me! Bakushin Bakushin Bakushin! Okay, again! Count to 894!
228.97: Concerts should be studied for just like tests! Let's Bakushin to the music!
228.98: With you by my side, I can overcome any race. I'll prove that to you. ♪
228.100: I won't let anything get in the way of my running or my singing. ♪ That's how an Umadol rolls. ☆
228.101: I really like the album cover too. ♪ That's something you have to pay attention to as an Umadol!
228.102: I uploaded an UmaTok of this dance and it exploded! Actual peak choreography.
228.103: This song really hits right now... Been going through some stuff with the gals. I should probably apologize, shouldn't I...
228.104: I'm gonna do my nails, so can you put on something upbeat?
228.105: I'll prove that I'm the fastest! That I deserve to stand center stage!
228.106: I was listening to this with Ticket and she broke down crying all of a sudden... Never a quiet moment with her.
228.107: Just pick what you want. I'm fine with whatever.
228.108: Un... unlimited... impact? Oh, I get it! Like kaboom! Right?
228.109: Umapyoi, umapyoi. ♪ This song's fun when we all sing it together! Pyoi, pyoi, pyoooi!
228.110: My favorite is... Hehe. All of them!
228.111: As long as the Great Shiraoki is watching over me, I can make destiny my own!
228.112: I'm so lucky I get to spend these shining days surrounded by friends... Fortune must be on my side!
228.113: Woiya... Haiya... Which will be your lucky song?
228.114: I got to do a concert with Opera O... hehe. I-I kind of want to dance more. I know that's silly, but...
228.115: The goddess of victory would never notice me... B-but if I keep trying, maybe I'll have a chance one day!
228.116: Which song is your fray... fav... fraywit? Ahh, I'm sorry!
228.117: For the life of me, I can't dance this with a serious face. My default expression is so relaxed, you know? I dunno, I just like... ughh!
228.118: Trying to get some youthful passion in your system? Or are you saying you want to run for your dreams with me? ...That was a joke.
228.119: This kinda reminds me of home. My parents used to play a lot of these at the bar... It takes me back.
228.120: The tempo befits a first-rate runner, and the fastest one at that. It's like this song was made for me!
228.121: The song is busy, but that's part of the charm. I hear it whenever I get together with Spe and co, so it's burned into my brain now.
228.122: Ohoho! I grant you permission to choose a song of your liking!
228.123: Oh... Didn't know you liked this kind of music. Hmm, I guess you've got decent taste.
228.124: Oh, so this is the kind of music you listen to. Mind if I join you?
228.125: Won't you take me on a musical adventure?
228.126: This thing really free? Well, what're ya waitin' for? We gotta listen to all the songs at least once!
228.128: Any recommendations, Trainer? It might be fun to look into the song's history together.
228.129: ...If you want to clear your mind, having a song play in the background is better than sitting in silence.
228.130: From festive fun to tender tears, there's a song for every occasion!
228.131: Ooh, this makes me want to burst out in song! C'mon, let's do a duet!
228.132: Elegant, touching, and splendidly cheerful... All elements that make this song perfect for a winning concert.
228.133: I love this song. ♪ The precise choreography lets me express myself down to my very fingertips.
228.134: Performing this song live gets me fired up—literally! The dancers at the edges always get a little singed... Ha, just kiddin'!
228.135: This song reminds me of a blooming flower bud... Like it's the starting line to the dream ahead!
228.136: To sing this on stage amidst the thunderous music and dazzling lights... There could be no greater honor.
228.137: This song is special, so... If you're going to listen with me, no talking until it's over.
228.138: Hearing this song brings back memories of close races and festive concerts. It makes me want to break into a run!
228.139: I always gotta squeeze the mic real hard when performing this! It's just so cool!
228.140: I've come to associate this song with memories of sparkling, passionate races. Hehe, it makes me want to run! ♪
228.141: We've practiced this song so much at karaoke it's become a specialty. ♪ Next chance we get, we'll sing it for you.
228.142: This song's a banger, am I right? I love the way it makes me feel like I'm the wind, just like when I'm runnin'.
228.143: Talk about some touching lyrics! Makes you think of all the people who've helped you get this far...
228.144: A wonderful, inspiring song. It helps me believe in the time I've spent at this academy, as well as the days to come! ♪
228.145: I have to sing this at the next karaoke sesh! In fact, I'll message Nature, Ikuno, and Turbo right now... ♪
228.146: I recall enjoying this song in the passenger seat of Maruzensky's car. It brings to mind runners cutting a dashing figure, no?
228.147: Oh hey, I sang this with Falco and Fine at karaoke. They even taught me the moves!
228.148: There are so many fun songs it's hard to pick! ♪
228.90: "Even if the whole world turns against us..." This part always makes my heart skip a beat. ♪ It's perfect for a princess and her prince!
228.127: "Music is the bean paste to the bun of your heart." I want to know what flavors you like!

<size=27>The snow in my hometown was quiet and pure, 
and it was white as far as eyes could see. 
It's truly one of my most precious and nostalgic sceneries. 
I wanted to be able to express how I feel about it… to you. 
I want to keep running alongside you to the end of this landscape. 
</size>

A New Year countdown party is to be held at Tracen Academy. 
Preparations are well underway as all Umamusume look to send 
their gratitude to the fans who supported them over the year. 
Among them, Duramente, Royce and Royce, and Cheval Grand 
each harbor their own feelings within their hearts. Will they find an 
answer to their doubts within the exciting fan-centric atmosphere?

205.1: I'll run with everything I have and won't stop until I'm the top Umamusume in all of Japan!
205.2: Carrot hamburger steaks, pasta, and also omlette rice! Wait, but which one was for good luck?
205.3: Oh, I keep my eye on the green be... Hey, I can't reveal my secrets!
205.4: I've taken up reading, though I have a hard time understanding all the theory behind training.
205.5: Um, enough that my roommate was surprised I could run so much.
205.6: When I'm running I block out all sound... But hearing cheers after I pass the post feels good.
205.7: Super confident! ♪ I'm the world's best Umamusume, after all!
205.8: Heheh. ♪ Get ready! I'm gonna dazzle on the track!
205.9: Of course I did! And everyone reading this should too! ♪
205.10: I clock out at five and enjoy my me time! I also love cutting loose on a Friday. ♪
205.11: A-okay! In fact, I'd say I'm feeling pretty rad. ♪
205.12: When I shift into top gear and start zooming like a hot rod!
205.13: Oguri was sleepwalking and ate all the rice in our rice cooker. I couldn't believe it!
205.14: If top quality entertainment is what you want, then look no further.
205.15: The musical "White Shoes Minuet" was wonderful. The ballet dancers had me entranced.
205.16: Every day? Always sleep well, eat well and... eat well.
205.17: ...The roads here are like a maze. I get lost sometimes.
205.18: I'll visit my hometown, of course... grrrowl... Well, after I eat.
205.19: To my spiny lobster sister who was separated from me at birth... You can't make red miso from the Kuroshio!
205.20: I like to sort oysters by where they were caught. I've always stood up for justice.
205.21: When I got the bright idea to cover myself in cement from the neck down, I made my peace with the world.
205.22: Well, you came to the right person. Wink. Was that cool, or what?
205.23: No comment... Hahaaa! I've always wanted to say that!
205.24: Heh, there's one I definitely don't wanna lose to! But it's cool, 'cause I'm gonna crush 'em anyway!
205.25: One hundred, of course. I'll show you a flawless race!
205.26: I wouldn't be me if I weren't aiming for number one, because I love to be number one. ♪
205.27: Not really. The others can act cool or clamor for attention all they want. I couldn't care less.
205.28: Never skip breakfast! I had a whole pound of steak this mornin'!
205.29: I balance my mind with zen meditation! Too much 'n it'll make ya all sleepy, though.
205.30: Once, I partied late with my racin' partner and had to get up real early the next day! Now talk about tough!
205.31: Excessive strain can lead to injury. It's best to go with the flow and wait for the opportune moment.
205.32: I wouldn't say so. The more you learn about Japanese culture, the more you realize how little you truly know.
205.33: I wonder... Everyone has their own ideas. Would you like to find out for yourself? Hehe...
205.34: Someone replaced our ketchup with El's super-spicy sauce yesterday...
205.35: I started cutting carrots into little stars for dinner. Just decided to try it one day, and now they're a big hit!
205.36: Having the guts to give it everything you got and never give up!
205.37: I've never felt burdened by my status. The Mejiro name is a source of pride and motivation for me.
205.38: Winning with grace, I suppose. But if the race goes down to the wire, appearances matter little.
205.39: Not exactly... Gold Ship has been deep-frying donuts, as if to tempt me personally!
205.40: Secret? No, no, no. There's no secret! My strength is loud! My strength is palpable!
205.41: The earth will shatter! The sky will fall! And I will be very sad...
205.42: Wha?! Wow, uhh, wonder what they could be. Probably just crows. Yep!
205.43: Losing your spark is no cause for despair. Rejoice at the chance to run alongside the Centurial Overlord!
205.44: I once endured a grueling test of survival on a deserted island. There were no mirrors, not even an audience to applaud my efforts!
205.45: I am always at one hundred percent! No peaks, no crescendos! Haaa ha ha ha!
205.47: My sister made me hold them. That's it.
205.48: Hmph. What fun would there be in that?
205.49: I will be victorious in this race. Witness with your own eyes true magnificence!
205.50: Yes! A toast for victory. With eggcellence for added fuel.
205.51: One puddle cannot halt an emperor's advance. I simply set my sights on the peak and show the world how to climb.
205.52: I only believe in my own strength... and, well, I consider it a lucky day if I see new flowers growing.
205.53: I'd be lying if I said no, but I've never considered it overbearing. Everything is a learning experience.
205.54: Train to the point where you are amazed by your own skills. Nervousness is nothing next to confidence.
205.55: Another action-packed day! I'm gonna hit the frontlines! WHOO!
205.56: Hwha! You mean, like, pick a kami oshi?! I-I can't do that! I adore all my oshis!
205.57: Follow your passion and run with your heart! At the end of it all, you'll shine the brightest!
205.58: Hmm, good question. Sometimes I get a catch, sometimes I don't. Sometimes I just fall asleep.
205.59: Great. We took another nap together yesterday. The weather was nice.
205.60: Hmmm... Just take it easy and wait for your time, I guess. Nya-ha-ha.
205.61: I ain't got no time to think about crazy what-ifs. Zoom straight to first—that's how ya win.

232.1: Actually, I dropped my lucky charm during the race... But aside from that, I'd rate my performance 10/10!

232.3: Hm? Oh... you're right. So many people are cheering me on.
232.4: Hmm... Ah. I was thinking I'd like to get a new pair of shoes after the race.
232.5: Heh heh heh! They sure did! But their toughness only highlighted my Teio tenacity!
232.6: Yeah! I totally recommend it! Buuut, I'm fast without it too!
232.7: Right now, I'm wicked into having spaghetti with panna cotta for dessert! ♪
232.8: I try not to stay bummed out! A leisurely drive chases all my blues away. ♪
232.9: Alas, I did not prepare a victory trick... Oh? What's that above your head?
232.10: Save those words for my next race—for there, you shall be dazzled even more!
232.11: Well... At our school cafeteria, I usually start by ordering the carrot... (See the full menu in our Ogurin Eats third-page special!)
232.12: I went to bed early and had a good night's rest. ...Huh? That's not what you're asking?
232.13: I'm as fit as a fiddle thanks to my daily routine! I made sure to do my femoral stretches yesterday!
232.14: A day off! 'Smatter of fact, I marked every day on the dorm calendar as a lucky day!
232.15: I'm happy, of course, but I ain't gettin' complacent—I'm only as good as I was yesterday!
232.16: Partner running, endurance competitions... Why the hell do I always think back to her?!
232.17: Well, of course... um, I respect my trainer greatly. What else can I say, except that there's no better teacher out there for me. ♪
232.18: I feel grateful to my fans, the support staff, and everyone who cheered for me! ♪ ...And my trainer too.
232.19: Visualization's key! Before ya start running, ya gotta line up the goal in your sights, then—BANG!
232.20: I eat, sleep, and play! ...Hrngh, guess that's not much different from normal, huh?
232.21: I was reciting the names of my opponents as I pondered every possible outcome... and the race turned out exactly as I imagined.
232.22: I hope I did you all proud. Nothing would make me happier.
232.23: Sounds great! Check this out—it's the victory pose Biko came up with!
232.24: I'm looking forward to burning up the track with you all in a race like this someday soon!
232.25: I'm pleased to hear that. I had my signature racewear ironed—it, too, is without a single wrinkle.
232.26: Yes, recording the baseball game really paid... Ahem! I mean, my strict discipline paid off.
232.27: Well said! I am the Phantom Bird—there's no limit to the heights I'll soar!
232.28: Of course! What better way to recharge your batteries than with the electrifying zing of a good jalapeño?
232.29: Your generous applause, praise, and cheers have adorned my glorious victory! For that, you have my thanks!
232.30: My elegant arrival at the starting gate! Did you see my eyes, brimming with apprehension? Ah, such beauty ought to be a sin!
232.31: It was just a lunch I was given—nothing more, nothing less.
232.32: I'll tear the competition to shreds. End of story.
232.33: Thank you... but allow me to make one correction. It was not pressure that moved me, but duty.
